node.title: Omicron: High demand for Covid-19 testing in Auckland causing delays
node.description: Lengthy queues are being reported at Covid-19 testing centres in Auckland for the second day in a row.
node.content:
["Lengthy queues are being reported at Covid-19 testing centres in Auckland for the second day in a row.", "", "
\nPhoto: Supplied / Te Wh\u0101nau O Waipareira\n
", "The Northern Region Health Coordination Centre said it was recording very high demand, similar to the peak of the Delta outbreak.", "Due to a long line of cars waiting outside a testing site in Botany, Auckland Transport is warning people to expect delays and detours for four bus services.", "Health authorities are asking people to stay away from testing sites unless they have cold or flu symptoms, have been at a location of interest, or have been asked to get tested by a health official.", "The Ministry of Health said unnecessary testing could delay results for people who urgently needed them."]
